Class FlexLayout

Static Fields
child: FlexLayoutChild
container: FlexLayoutContainer
Constructors
FlexLayout()

A utility class for working with flex layouts.

Ex: 

FlexLayout.container.vertical(parent);
FlexLayout.child.grab(child1, 0);
FlexLayout.child.grab(child2, 20);
See http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-flexbox/

static FlexLayoutChild child
static FlexLayoutContainer container

FlexLayout()

Class YesNoDialog extends BAlert

Constructors
YesNoDialog(String dialogTitle, String dialogMessage, List<dynamic> buttonText)
Methods
getResponse(): Future<int>

Create a YesNoDialog dialog. It is possible to have more then two buttons by passing in a list of button names in the constructor. An instance of a YesNoDialog can only be used once.
